com.whirvis.jraknet.client

Interface RakNetClientListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BroadcastTest.ServerDiscoveryListener, ChatClient, RakNetClient, RakNetClientBundleExample

    public interface RakNetClientListener
    This interface is used by the RakNetClient to let the user know when specific events are triggered. Do not use any sleep methods that will cause the client thread to pause, as it will cause a timeout.
    Author:
    Trent "Whirvis" Summerlin

      • handleUnknownMessage

        default void handleUnknownMessage(RakNetServerSession session,
                                  RakNetPacket packet,
                                  int channel)
        Called when a packet with an ID below the user enumeration (ID_USER_PACKET_ENUM) cannot be handled by the session because it is not programmed to handle it. This function can be used to add missing features from the regular RakNet protocol that are absent in JRakNet if needed.
        Parameters:
        session - the server that sent the packet.
        packet - the packet received from the server.
        channel - the channel the packet was sent on.

      • handleNettyMessage

        default void handleNettyMessage(io.netty.buffer.ByteBuf buf,
                                java.net.InetSocketAddress address)
        Called when the handler receives a packet after the server has already handled it, this method is useful for handling packets outside of the RakNet protocol. However, be weary when using this as packets meant for the server will have already been handled by the client; and it is not a good idea to try to manipulate JRakNet's RakNet protocol implementation using this method.
        Parameters:
        buf - the packet buffer.
        address - the address of the sender.

      • onHandlerException

        default void onHandlerException(java.net.InetSocketAddress address,
                                java.lang.Throwable throwable)
        Called when a handler exception has occurred, these normally do not matter as long as it does not come the address of the server the client is connecting or is connected to.
        Parameters:
        address - the address that caused the exception.
        throwable - the Throwable that was caught.

      • onThreadException

        default void onThreadException(java.lang.Throwable throwable)
        Called when an exception is caught in the external thread the client is running on, this method is only called when the client is started through connectThreaded().
        Parameters:
        throwable - the Throwable that was caught.
